results.overview:
PS 506 is located in south Brooklyn's vibrant Sunset Park Community.  We believe that students learn best when educators create a safe, risk-free academic environment. Teachers provide meaningful, relevant, and challenging instruction by offering differentiated entry points, modeling expected outcomes and providing clear and specific next steps.  Students receive multiple opportunities to work collaboratively with peers. Students receive a well-rounded education with special programs, such as theater, and technology during the school day. PS 506 offers a Spanish dual language program for students in kindergarten through fifth grades. 

Students also have opportunities to engage in enrichment activities after school including running and soccer clubs, theater, STEAM and robotic classes. Families are welcome to the school for events such as Family Fun Days. Families are able to participate in fun classroom activities with their children.  The PTA also hosts monthly meetings with student performances.

PS 506 is a Leader in Me school, which teaches students, parents and staff about the, "Seven Habits of Highly Effective People," by Stephen Covey.  Students learn how to, "Be proactive; begin with the end in mind; put first things first; think win-win; seek first to understand, then to be understood; synergize; sharpen the saw."  These life skills help students set high expectations for themselves to be leaders so that they prioritize work, set goals for themselves, work well with others by listening, and balance elements of life.  Students have an opportunity to set personal and academic goals and monitor and track their progress.  Teachers assist in this process by modeling these processes and providing feedback around their goals and action plans.  PS 506 received Lighthouse Certification after outside reviewers observed the school using an extensive rubric to assess the integration of habits within our school community.  PS 506 was re-certified as a Lighthouse school in 2018.

As a Community School, PS 506 offers many services to our students and families, including our School Based Health and Dental clinic in partnership with NYU Langone.  PS 506 also works closely with Center for Family Life in partnership with the Office of Community Schools to provide additional support, such as after school academic and enrichment programming for students.

PS 506 works with many outside organizations . Some classes were partnered with Brooklyn Connections.  This program is designed to make the research process fun and accessible for students and educators. Fully aligned with the New York State Next Generation Learning Standards, Brooklyn Connections anchors students in the 21st Century learning skills needed in order to achieve academic success in school and beyond. Students at PS 506 also enjoy a full arts program.  We participate in Disney Musical in Schools Program in which students prepare and implement a full musical production.  PS 506 has partnered with Arts Connection as well as Dance Wave.  Teaching artists visit weekly and provide art residencies to all students in visual arts, dance, and drumming.

results.overview: P.S. 595 The Colibri Community School is a dual language school located in the Bronx. We are committed to cultivating biliterate students. Our school values are Equity, Family, Joy! We embody this in all we do from teaching to enrichment activities. Phipps Neighborhood is our Community Based Organization and offers extracurricular activities to students including afterschool programming. P.S. 595 serves all students and believes in the power of diversity and multi-language approaches. We also serve students with disabilities and have flexible learning environments with bilingual special education programs. We engage families through monthly workshops, meeting sessions with the Principal, visits to the classroom throughout the year, and much more! We are proud to serve 3K to 5th grade students and look forward to continued success!  This school has a Bilingual Special Education (BSE) program: Open to students recommended for Bilingual Special Education (BSE) on their Individualized Education Plan (IEP). If your child is recommended for BSE on their IEP and you have questions, visit www.schools.nyc.gov/specializedprograms or contact BSEprograms@schools.nyc.gov. The Autism Horizon Program supports students with autism in a special class with eight students, a special education teacher and paraprofessional with emphasis on building skills and offering opportunities for meaningful inclusion in larger settings. Students in this program may need additional academic support and require speech and language services, including in areas of social or pragmatic communication. For more information, speak with your CSE or IEP team and refer to Specialized Programs for Students with Disabilities (nyc.gov).

results.overview: P.S. 770 is a unique and diverse choice elementary school in District 17. Due to being a choice school, families choose P.S. 770 from all over District 17 as well as neighboring districts in Brooklyn. Our school features and open classroom concept with teams of teachers that teacher every child. Starting in first grade, teams of teachers remain with your child from 1st-2nd grade and then 3rd-5th grade (looping model). Each grade in our school, K-5, has a Special Education Teacher (ICT on every grade) and we offer self contained (12:1:1) for K-2 and 3-5. Our unique model allows us to focus on every child and meet the needs of our diverse learners. All of our students are taught through our H.E.A.R.T.S. values and P.S. 770 has been identified as a Respect for All School for the past four years. All students at P.S. 770 receive PE, Music, and Dance and we provide 175 spots for free afterschool with Roads to Success. We also have partnerships with the Young People's Choir of New York City (YPC), CHAMPS, NYRR, and Music and the Brain. We pride ourselves on our focus on community, social/emotional learning, and joyous learning.
